        <updateDate>2021-03-01T21:00:16Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Making Pipelines Accountable to Consumers and Taxpayers Act or the</b> <b>MPACT Act</b></p> <p>This bill revises the authority of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) regarding rates and charges in connection with the transportation or sale of natural gas.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill </p> <ul> <li>provides FERC the authority to set a refund effective date and order a natural gas company to provide refunds when a rate or charge is unjust, unreasonable, unduly discriminatory, or preferential; and</li> <li>requires FERC to conduct a study on the impact of such authority on the cost of capital paid by natural gas companies and the average time it takes to resolve proceedings related to rate changes.</li> </ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
